        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl0_Label1"><p>November 26, 2014 Iperius Backup 4 has been officially released. It includes some new and important features: Online Backup to Microsoft Azure Storage Backup to external USB drives: now you can univocally identify a drive regardless of its drive letter (that can change) Backup to Dropbox: now you can do it directly into a subfolder (that can be created [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl0_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/iperius-backup-4-backup-azure-storage/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/restore-computer-from-system-image-backup/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Restore your computer from a system image backup</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_Label1"><p>Iperius Backup allows to create a system image backup for Windows. When you create a drive image, you can restore the whole computer in case of hardware failures, virus infections or system crashes. If you want to see how to make a system image backup, read the related tutorial: How to make a Drive Image with Iperius. This simple [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl1_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/restore-computer-from-system-image-backup/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-amazon-s3-with-iperius-complete-software/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Backup to Amazon S3 with Iperius</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_Label1"><p>Iperius is a very powerful and feature-rich software. Among its main features, it also includes the Amazon S3 backup, so the possibility to make online backups to the Amazon S3 cloud storage. In addition to the S3 backup, Iperius can use all the other major online storage platforms, such as Google Drive, OneDrive and Dropbox. In this [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl2_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-amazon-s3-with-iperius-complete-software/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-tape-lto-with-iperius-the-simple-and-secure-software/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Backup to Tape LTO with Iperius. The simple and secure software.</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_Label1"><p>LTO technology allows to store large amounts of data on magnetic tapes with a very low cost per GB. The LTO tapes are now widely used especially in big data environments, where databases and virtualization require high capacity storage media, reliability and performances. The estimated duration of the media is about 30 years, which makes LTO [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl3_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-tape-lto-with-iperius-the-simple-and-secure-software/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-dropbox-how-to-make-it-with-iperius/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Backup to Dropbox – How to make it with Iperius</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_Label1"><p>This tutorial shows how to make an automatic backup to Dropbox (online backup) using the Iperius cloud backup features. Iperius Backup can make backups also to other important cloud storage services, such as Google Drive, OneDrive and Amazon S3. Dropbox is a free file sharing service that can be also used as an online storage solution to save data to [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl4_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-to-dropbox-how-to-make-it-with-iperius/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-to-enable-google-drive-api-and-get-client-credentials/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">How to enable Google Drive API and get client credentials</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_Label1"><p>This tutorial shows how to enable the Google Drive API for a specific Google account, and get the access credentials to be used from Iperius to make cloud backups. In fact, to make an online backup to Google Drive you first need to enable some specific options, then you have to create an account into [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl5_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-to-enable-google-drive-api-and-get-client-credentials/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/system-image-backup-drive-image-with-iperius/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">System Image Backup (Drive Image) for Windows with Iperius</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_Label1"><p>Iperius is a powerful and complete backup software for Windows. Among its features, you have the full system image backup (Drive Image), that allows to backup and restore the entire system in a few clicks. The image backup is made automatically and without any service interruption or system reboot, therefore without interfering with the user work. [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl6_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/system-image-backup-drive-image-with-iperius/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl7_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-mysql-and-mariadb-databases-with-iperius/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Backup MySQL and MariaDB databases with Iperius</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl7_Label1"><p>With Iperius you can backup MySQL and MariaDB databases easily and efficiently. Iperius is a complete database backup software. It can back up local or remote databases without any service interruption (hot backup). Backup files can be automatically transferred by FTP, FTPS and SFTP or to Cloud services such as Google Drive, Dropbox or Amazon S3. With a single license [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl7_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/backup-mysql-and-mariadb-databases-with-iperius/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl8_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-to-activate-iperius-backup/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">How to activate Iperius Backup</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl8_Label1"><p>This brief tutorial explains how to activate Iperius Backup after you bought a commercial license. Below you can see the few simple steps to perform the activation of iperius: 1. Download and install the Free version of Iperius Backup: Click here to download Iperius Backup Free 2. Click on the activation button on the top right [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl8_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/how-to-activate-iperius-backup/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
    <br />
    
    <table style="border:solid 0px white; width:100%;">
        <tr>
            <td style="font-weight:bold; font-size:13pt;">
                <a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl9_HyperLink1" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/iperius-3-1-launch-backups-and-update-iperius-remotely/" target="_blank"><font color="#444444">Iperius 3.1 – Launch backups and update Iperius remotely</font></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><hr /></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>
                <span id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl9_Label1"><p>October 3, 2013 Iperius Backup 3.1 introduces several important features. Now from the Web Console you can perform a backup on the machine where Iperius is installed . You can launch without problems one or more backup jobs with a single click. Furthermore, you can also launch the Iperius AutoUpdate. You will no longer need [&hellip;]</p>
</span><a id="ctl00_cph1_LangUserControl_ListView1_ctrl9_HyperLink2" href="https://www.iperiusbackup.net/en/iperius-3-1-launch-backups-and-update-iperius-remotely/" target="_blank">Read more »»</a> 
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table> 
